        "title": "Add customizable Codex menu bar metrics",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n- Add an All metrics menu bar display mode for Codex usage\r\n- Show configurable session, weekly, pace, and reset segments\r\n- Add pace label styles and reset format options, including compact hybrid date/countdown formats\n- Persist the new preferences and refresh countdown-backed menu bar text when needed\n- Respect the selected app language, locale date order, and 12/24-hour preference in reset text and previews\n\r\n## Screenshots\r\n<img width=\"658\" height=\"862\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-15 at 11 39 11 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2e67bfe8-b3a6-4b57-a237-488072eaf632\" />\r\n<img width=\"658\" height=\"862\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-15 at 11 52 33 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b3db1e81-9ea1-471a-8bf0-6577125109b0\" />\r\n<img width=\"420\" height=\"42\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-16 at 12 09 03 AM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0bb9e9ee-5b48-4a3e-9ddc-a5d67a571f68\" />\r\n\r\nScreenshots attached showing:\r\n- compact all-metrics menu bar output\r\n- Display settings with Codex all-metrics toggles\r\n- reset format picker options\r\n\r\n## Exact-head validation\n\n- Exact head: `2b3e4d99006925b33795a4554a53baf474432551`\n- 63 focused reset, countdown, settings, and projection tests after the hidden-lane fallback repair\n- `make check`\n- `autoreview`: no accepted/actionable findings (`0.83`)\n- Earlier reviewed head: `./Scripts/compile_and_run.sh` (release build, full tests, signed package, relaunch, process-stability check)\n- Earlier packaged bundle visibly rendered `codexbar-merged` in the menu bar after relaunch; the latest exact-head delta is covered by a focused hidden-exhausted-lane regression\n\nPeekaboo identified the in-bounds status item, but its synthetic click did not open the menu on this host. Settings automation is therefore not counted as current exact-head UI proof; the attached contributor screenshots cover the settings layout and menu output.\n",
